16 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
17 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
18 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 1-451 of Title 63, unless there
19 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
20 A. There is hereby created within the State Department of
21 Health the Oklahoma Rare Disease Advisory Council.
22 B. The purpose of the Council shall be to provide guidance and
23 recommendations to educate the public, the Legislature, and other
24
Req. No. 12482 Page 1

1 stat e agencies, as appropriate, on the needs of individuals with
2 rare diseases living in this state.
3 C. The Council shall conduct the following activities to
4 benefit those impacted by rare diseases in this state:
5 1. Convene public hearings, make inquiries, and solicit
6 comments from the general public in Oklahoma to assist the Council
7 with a first-year landscape or survey of the needs of rare disease
8 patients, caregivers, and providers in the state;
9 2. Provide testimony and comments on pending legislation and
10 regulations before the Legislature, if called, and other state
11 agencies that impact Oklahoma's rare disease community;
12 3. Consult with experts on rare diseases to develop policy
13 recommendations to improve patient access to, and quality of, rare
14 disease specialists, affordable and comprehensive health care
15 coverage, relevant diagnostics, timely treatment, and other needed
16 services;
17 4. Establish best practices and protocols to include in-state
18 planning related to natural disasters, public health emergencies, or
19 other emergency declarations to enable continuity of care for rare
20 disease patients and ensure safeguards against discrimination for
21 rare disease patients are in place;
22 5. Identify areas of unmet need for research and opportunities
23 for collaboration across stakeholders and other state rare disease
24
