1 advi sory councils that can inform future studies and work done by
2 the Council; and
3 6. Research and identify best practices to reduce health
4 disparities and achieve health equity in the research, diagnosis,
5 and treatment of rare disease in this state.
6 D. 1. The Council's appointment process shall be conducted in
7 a transparent manner to provide interested individuals an
8 opportunity to apply for membership on the Council. All members of
9 the Council shall be full-time residents of this state as
10 practicable. Membership shall include a diverse set of stakeholders
11 representative of the geographic and population diversity of the
12 state.
13 2. The Governor shall appoint the chair of the Council not
14 later than December 1, 2025. The chair shall not hold any position
15 within the government of this state.
16 3. The Governor shall appoint seven (7) members:
17 a. two patients who have a rare disease,
18 b. two caregivers of a person with a rare disease,
19 c. one representative of the biopharmaceutical industry,
20 d. one representative of a rare disease patient
21 organization that operates in this state, and
22 e. one representative of a health plan company.
23 4. The State Department of Health shall appoint five (5)
24 members:
