3 E. 1. The Council shall electronically submit a report to the
4 President Pro Tempore of the Oklahoma State Senate, the Speaker of
5 the Oklahoma House of Representatives, and the Governor within one
6 (1) year of establishment of the Oklahoma Rare Disease Advisory
7 Council and annually thereafter. Prior to submission, a draft of
8 the annual report shall be made available for public comment and
9 discussed at an open public meeting.
10 2. The annual reports shall:
11 a. describe the activities and progress of the Council
12 under this section, and
13 b. provide recommendations to the Legislature and
14 Governor on ways to address the needs of people living
15 with rare diseases in this state.
16 F. 1. The initial meeting of the Council shall occur no later
17 than February 1, 2026. Thereafter, the Council shall meet no less
18 than quarterly.
19 2. The Council shall:
20 a. provide opportunities for the public to hear updates
21 and provide input into its work, and
22 b. create and maintain a public website where meeting
23 minutes, notices of upcoming meetings, and public
24 comments may be submitted.
