11 fill such vacancy in a timely manner and in compliance with
12 requirements set forth in subsection D of this section.
13 H. As used in this section, "rare disease", also known as an
14 orphan disease, means a disease that affects fewer than two hundred
15 thousand (200,000) people in the United States.
